[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The comment says "In production, use the model's variance estimates or ensemble disagreement" but doesn't clarify that this approximation has no statistical basis and produces intervals that are completely disconnected from the model's actual uncertainty. A learner might carry this pattern forward thinking it's a reasonable placeholder.
