[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The negation is correct (higher partial hazard means shorter survival, so you negate to align with the concordance_index expectation that higher predicted value = longer time). However, the comment "negative because higher hazard = shorter time" is incomplete. The `concordance_index` from lifelines expects that a higher predicted value corresponds to a longer event time. The negation converts "higher hazard" to "lower predicted survival time" which then needs to be negated again to become "higher value = longer time." The comment should explain the full chain.
